# bar-metrics — environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in real values. Never commit secrets;
# `.env*` is gitignored (this `.env.example` is the one tracked exception).
#
# The app skeleton (issue #2) needs NO environment variables to boot — this file
# documents the pattern and lists the variables later slices will introduce so
# the runbook stays one source of truth.

# --- Later slices (NOT required to run the skeleton) ---

# Neon application database — app-owned tables, later Auth.js sessions
# (issue #4 / ADR 0003). Two URLs to the same Neon database:
#   - DATABASE_URL: POOLED (PgBouncer) connection — used by the app at runtime
#     (serverless-safe). Its host contains "-pooler".
#   - DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED: DIRECT (unpooled) connection — used only by Prisma
#     Migrate (PgBouncer's transaction pooling breaks migrations).
# The Neon/Vercel integration injects both names automatically; `vercel env
# pull` writes them into `.env.local`.
# DATABASE_URL=
# DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED=

# Read-only connection to the legacy nubebar Postgres read-model (issue #5 /
# ADR 0003). Must point at a DigitalOcean Connection Pool (PgBouncer-backed),
# not the cluster's raw connection string — required for Vercel's serverless
# functions (ADR 0003). See README -> Environment for how to create the pool.
# DigitalOcean's managed Postgres uses a self-signed CA, so the URL needs
# `?sslmode=no-verify` (still TLS-encrypted, just skips chain verification).
# NUBEBAR_DATABASE_URL=

# Reserved for the future locked-down read-only Postgres role the chatbot's
# SQL escape-hatch tool will be forced through, with RLS enforcing per-tenant
# sucursal scoping (ADR 0002 / build step 4). NOT created or used yet — this
# slice (#5) only reserves the name; do not wire it up.
# NUBEBAR_AGENT_DATABASE_URL=

# Auth.js v5 session-encryption secret (issue #11 / ADR 0002). Generate one
# locally with `npx auth secret` (writes to .env.local) or any sufficiently
# random string (e.g. `openssl rand -base64 32`). Required for Auth.js to
# encrypt session cookies; never commit the real value.
# AUTH_SECRET=

# Resend API key for the magic-link sign-in provider (issue #11 / ADR 0002 —
# Resend is the sole sign-in provider, no OAuth, no Credentials). Create a
# free Resend account at https://resend.com, generate an API key under
# API Keys, and paste it into .env.local — never into chat, an issue, or a PR.
# AUTH_RESEND_KEY=

# The verified sender address magic-link emails are sent from (issue #11).
# Use a domain you've verified in Resend, or Resend's onboarding/sandbox
# sender for local testing. See README -> Environment for the setup steps.
# AUTH_EMAIL_FROM=

# Anthropic API key for the tool-calling chatbot (ADR 0001 / 0004).
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
